thread.title: Dallas Cowboys QB Branden Weeden: 'I'm pissed' about being removed as starter
thread.title_full: Dallas Cowboys QB Branden Weeden: 'I'm pissed' about being removed as starter

title: Dallas Cowboys QB Branden Weeden: 'I'm pissed' about being removed as starter
text:
USA TODAY Sports' Tom Pelissero explains why the Cowboys will start Matt Cassel in place of Brandon Weeden. USA TODAY Sports
Brandon Weeden not happy about losing his starting job. (Photo: GETTY IMAGES)
IRVING, Texas - When asked how he felt about being demoted after three games as the Dallas Cowboys starting quarterback, Brandon Weeden didn’t hold back.
“How do you think I took it?” Weeden said Wednesday. “Obviously I’m pissed.”
Weeden, who lost all three games as the Cowboys starter, has been benched by the coaching staff in favor of veteran Matt Cassel, who was acquired in a late-September trade with the Buffalo Bills.
“I told them (coaching staff) how I felt,” Weeden said. “They know how I feel. They know I’m pissed.”
USA TODAY
Cowboys coach Jason Garrett says QB change needed to 'spark' the offense
After throwing for 188 yards and one interception in Sunday’s 30-6 loss to the New England Patriots, Weeden was informed by the coaching staff on Tuesday that he would serve as Cassel’s backup in the Cowboys’ next game, Oct. 25 at the New York Giants.
Weeden said he would handle the decision “as a pro,” not make excuses and not “throw a pity party for myself.”
Asked if he was being made a scapegoat for an offense that has struggled on several levels, Weeden said, “You guys can dictate however you want to perceive it. I’m not going to comment on it. Like I said, I don’t want to bring the attention to me. I don’t want to say something I shouldn’t say. I’ve got my feelings. I’m going to keep them to myself and go from there.”
